content:
Review these recommended technical requirements to get the best performance out of Salesforce reports and dashboards.

These technical requirements are provided to help you predict whether your hardware and network can provide an acceptable and productive user experience. Salesforce strongly recommends testing the actual end-user experience with a configuration identical to what you expect to use in production.

For the fastest and most stable experience, we recommend:

An Octane 2.0 score of 30,000
Network latency of 150 ms or lower
Download speed of 3 Mbps or higher
At least 8 GB of RAM, with 3 GB available for Salesforce browser tabs

Minimum requirements are:

An Octane 2.0 score of 20,000
Network latency of 200 ms or lower
Download speed of 1 Mbps
At least 5 GB of RAM, with 2 GB available for Salesforce browser tabs

To get your Octane 2.0 score, latency, and download speed, append speedtest.jsp to your orgâ€™s domain.

We recommend running this test on the same hardware, network, physical location, and browser as your users. Improving page load times is most important, followed by improving Octane 2.0 scores and tab longevity.

Using newer-generation hardware with faster CPUs generates higher Octane 2.0 scores.
Using the latest version of Salesforce-supported browsers generates higher Octane 2.0 scores.

IE11 results in low Octane 2.0 scores and slower page load speeds.

Improving virtual desktop environment performance is also crucial, especially when using dedicated desktops or reducing users per environment can improve performance.
title: Salesforce Lightning Reports and Dashboards Technical Requirements
